{
  "number": 1893,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1893",
  "title": "Multiple instantsearch queryHook",
  "body": "When using multiple instantsearch (instantsearch with multiple index)\r\n\r\nYou have:\r\n- several instantsearch instance (1 per index)\r\n- 1 searchbox widget\r\n- different hits widget for each instance\r\n\r\nIf you are using queryHook, the callback you give is call one time per instantsearch instance.\r\nBut I did not find a way to know which instantsearch instance is currently being \"hooked\".\r\n\r\nProbably having the index name as one of the parameters of the hook would be better.\r\n\r\nRight you kind of need to hack by creating several searchbox widget for each instance which is not the most logical.",
